## Example 5 ‚Äî Solve Equations with [\ln] Terms

Solve each equation. Round to the nearest ten-thousandth.

### Step 1: Use Properties to Combine Logarithms

[\ln (x - 6) = 1] ‚Üí [x - 6 = e^1] ‚Üí [x = e + 6 \approx 2.718 + 6 = 8.718]

[\ln (x + 2) = 3] ‚Üí [x + 2 = e^3] ‚Üí [x = e^3 - 2 \approx 20.086 - 2 = 18.086]

[\ln (x + 3) = 5] ‚Üí [x + 3 = e^5] ‚Üí [x = e^5 - 3 \approx 148.413 - 3 = 145.413]

[\ln 3x + \ln 2x = 9] ‚Üí [\ln (6x^2) = 9] ‚Üí [6x^2 = e^9] ‚Üí [x^2 = \frac{e^9}{6} \approx \frac{8103.084}{6} \approx 1350.514] ‚Üí [x \approx \sqrt{1350.514} \approx 36.75]

[\ln 5x + \ln x = 7] ‚Üí [\ln (5x^2) = 7] ‚Üí [5x^2 = e^7] ‚Üí [x^2 = \frac{e^7}{5} \approx \frac{1096.633}{5} \approx 219.327] ‚Üí [x \approx \sqrt{219.327} \approx 14.81]

[\ln 3x = 2] ‚Üí [3x = e^2] ‚Üí [x = \frac{e^2}{3} \approx \frac{7.389}{3} \approx 2.463]

## Example 6 ‚Äî Continuously Compounded Interest

### Step 1: Solve Part a ‚Äî Find Balance After 5 Years

[A = Pe^{rt}] with [P = 4000], [r = 0.034], [t = 5].
[A = 4000e^{0.034(5)} = 4000e^{0.17} \approx 4000(1.1853) \approx 4741.20]

The balance is approximately $4741.20.

### Step 2: Solve Part b ‚Äî Time to Reach $6000

[6000 = 4000e^{0.034t}]
[1.5 = e^{0.034t}]
[\ln 1.5 = 0.034t]
[t = \frac{\ln 1.5}{0.034} \approx \frac{0.4055}{0.034} \approx 11.93] years

### Step 3: Solve Part c ‚Äî Principal for $10,000 in 10 Years

[10000 = Pe^{0.034(10)} = Pe^{0.34}]
[P = \frac{10000}{e^{0.34}} \approx \frac{10000}{1.4049} \approx 7119.44]

Monique should invest approximately $7119.44.

### Step 4: Apply to Sarita's Account

For [P = 750], [r = 0.027], [t = 3]:
[A = 750e^{0.027(3)} = 750e^{0.081} \approx 750(1.0843) \approx 813.23]

For time to reach $2000:
[2000 = 750e^{0.027t}]
[2.667 = e^{0.027t}]
[t = \frac{\ln 2.667}{0.027} \approx \frac{0.9808}{0.027} \approx 36.33] years

For principal to have $1000 in 5 years:
[1000 = Pe^{0.027(5)} = Pe^{0.135}]
[P = \frac{1000}{e^{0.135}} \approx \frac{1000}{1.1447} \approx 873.64]

